clude non-integer solutions.\"", "\"HEURISTIC METHODS\":\"Heuristic methods are problem-solving techniques that use practical approaches to find good-enough solutions when exact methods are too costly or time-consuming.\"", "\"METAHEURISTIC METHODS\":\"Metaheuristic methods are higher-level procedures designed to find, generate, or select a heuristic that may provide a sufficiently good solution to an optimization problem.\"", "\"GENETIC ALGORITHMS\":\"Genetic algorithms are search heuristics that mimic the process of natural selection to generate high-quality solutions to optimization and search problems.\"", "\"SIMULATED ANNEALING\":\"Simulated annealing is a probabilistic technique for approximating the global optimum of a given function. It is useful for large optimization problems.\"", "\"TABU SEARCH\":\"Tabu search is a metaheuristic search method that guides a local heuristic search procedure to explore the solution space beyond local optimality.\"", "\"ANT COLONY OPTIMIZATION\":\"Ant colony optimization is a probabilistic technique for solving computational problems which can be reduced to finding good paths through graphs.\"", "\"PARTICLE SWARM OPTIMIZATION\":\"Particle swarm optimization is a computational method that optimizes a problem by iteratively trying to improve a candidate solution with regard to a given measure of quality.\"", "\"CONSTRAINT PROGRAMMING\":\"Constraint programming is a paradigm for solving combinatorial problems that involves stating constraints that need to be satisfied and finding solutions that meet these constraints.\"", "\"FEASIBILITY STUDY\":\"A feasibility study is an assessment of the practicality of a proposed plan or method. It evaluates the likelihood of the plan's success.\""], "parameters": {"model": "text-embedding-3-small", "temperature": 0.0, "frequency_penalty": null, "presence_penalty": null, "top_p": 1.0, "max_tokens": 4000, "n": 1}}